title: For Sale:  World War II Walther PP
postcontent:
I have a 1945 manufactured Walther PP that was brought back to the US by a WWII soldier. This is an "ac" marked gun, also known as a "cigarette gun" or "last ditch gun" because these were being built as the Americans were nearing the Walther factory so they were being built with little regard to finish or looks, just as long as they functioned so the German soldiers were not without weapons. With that being said, the finish is a little rough, but a unique thing about this gun is that the numbers actually match, most ac variations aren't numbers matching. The bore is bright and shiny and has excellent rifling. Gun appears to be fully functional and although I've never tried firing it I see no reason why it couldn't be fired.  

This also comes with the holster that it was brought back with it. The holster is also authentic and correct for World War II and valued at $90-$120 

I value this package at around $1000 to the right collector. I know its hard to find the right collector... So I'm asking $700 for the gun and holster for a quick sale. 

Please contact me for additional photos of gun and holster, I can only upload one picture here.

title: For Sale:  Beretta 90-Two .40 S&W
postcontent:
This is a brand new in the box and unfired Beretta 90-Two in .40 S&W.  This pistol is Italian made.

This pistol was custom designed by Beretta to fire the .40 S&W so the slide, springs and buffer are slightly heavier than the Model 96.  Like the 92/96, it is double/single action.  A rail mount and rail cover was added to meet the needs of the two primary markets for the pistol: law enforcement and military special operations.  The pistol was poorly marketed (beginning with the name) and eventually dropped by Beretta.  However, those who know Beretta pistols, know that this Italian made pistol is one of Beretta's finest.

For those new to the .40 S&W, it is a formidable round. Firing the Hornady 155 gr XTP or 180 gr XTP the .40 S&W delivers 479 ft-lb of energy at the muzzle; this matches the energy delivered by the venerable .45 auto and 40% more energy than the 9mm. This is accomplished while keeping felt recoil comparable to the 9mm. This massive increase in energy is why the U.S. military plans to replace the 9mm pistol with .40 S&W.

This BNIB pistol comes in the factory box with two magazines and all factory paperwork; a set of Beretta Thin-Grips is also included.  The pistol has been upgraded to include a steel guide rod.

USPS Priority Mail shipping is $20.00.
